<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 10. Basidiospore shape and size in all studied species of Subulicystidium. Each species is illustrated by a single specimen and herbarium codes are indicated on the figure." , "Figure 5. Species of Subulicystidium with broad cylindric basidiospores. Subulicystidium oberwinkleri (KAS: L 1860, holotype): a cystidia b basidiospores. Subulicystidium nikau (KAS: L 1296): c cystidia d basidiospores. Subulicystidium boidinii (KAS: L 1584 a, holotype): e mature hymenium f young hymenium g basidiospores. All preparations done in 3 % aqueous solution of potassium hydroxide (KOH) mixed with 1 % aqueous solution of Phloxine. All scale bars equal 10 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/213733" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/213726" .

